    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.24/3–447: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 4, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>263. After consultation with Brit and unless you perceive objection, please
                    inform Greek Govt we studying possibility supplying some of equipment required
                    by Greek armed forces. As guide and basis for this Greeks should immediately
                    submit through you formal detailed request for all essential items Brit not able
                    furnish. Indication relative <pb facs="0101" n="87" xml:id="pg_87"/> importance
                    and urgency different items would be useful. Telegraph full summary articles and
                    quantities desired.</p>
                <p>For your info we already actively considering Greek supply needs as presented by
                    Brit. Greek request desired primarily to serve as formal basis for action and
                    also as check on Brit figures. Any comments you or <gloss target="#t_MA1"
                        >MA</gloss> feel able make on Brit or Greek estimates in light present
                    situation would be welcome. Comments Brit military mission on Greek request also
                    desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
